    "intro": "The five movements below trace the chapter's argument from the closing of the Abraham era through the birthright transaction, attending throughout to the author's theological intent within Genesis and the canonical resonance across the rest of Scripture. Where Hebrew vocabulary sharpens an English translation, a brief note follows the movement.",
